Power provider Eskom has seconded group capital executive Abram Masango to the office of the group CE, to further strengthen the implementation of Eskom&rsquo;s corporate plan. Eskom interim CEO Matshela Koko said the move was part of the company&rsquo;s design-to-cost five-year strategic corporate plan, which continued to gain momentum. In his new role, Masango will assist Eskom CFO Anoj Singh and Koko with the execution of the 2017/18 corporate plan. &ldquo;Masango has the appropriate skills needed to ensure focused execution, with the determined leadership to manage the daunting work ahead,&rdquo; added Koko. Meanwhile, Eskom capital assurance, integration and special projects GM Prish Govender will act as group capital executive with immediate effect.